&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 2 HCA posts- Alex Frailty Community Ward&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Surrey Downs Health and Care have developed a new model of care transforming post-acute and community rehabilitation care for frail patients whose needs can be met outside of an acute setting. This care is provided in Alex Frailty Community Ward. Alex Ward provide a short term bedded facility, as well as intensive therapy, re-ablement and care planning support offering a holistic approach to care and allowing patients to maintain their level of health and independence and move to a more appropriate setting of care as quickly as possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What are we looking for? &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking to recruit experienced Band 2 HCAs to join the dedicated multidisciplinary team here in Alex Frailty Community Unit. This an exciting opportunity to further develop core skills and consolidate previous experiences gained. You will be working within a multidisciplinary team with the support of senior staff delivering care to a high standard.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So, if you’re looking for a different type of NHS employer that is working to push beyond and remove traditional boundaries and barriers, bringing care to patients when and where they need it, and you want to work alongside motivated, passionate and visionary colleagues, come and work for SDHC!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PLEASE NOTE:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to high number of applications this vacancy may be closed earlier than advertised.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kathryn Maskens - Ward Manager&lt;/p&gt;
